public class IMRParameterChangeListener
extends java.lang.Object
implements IMRParameterChangeListenerAPI

Title: BJF_1997_IMRParameterChangeListener
Description: Listens for Parameter changes, i.e. from user modification in the GUI, and if the y-Axis is changed, makes visible the IML Parameter if Exceed Probability is choosen for the Y-Axis. Otherwise it ensures that the IML ParameterEditor is invisible

setControlParameterListEditor

public void setControlParameterListEditor(ParameterListEditor control)
This function sets the paramater list editor that is the gui editor for paramater list of the control paramaters. These paramaters are used for setting the x and y axis along with the IMT.

parameterChange

public void parameterChange(ParameterChangeEvent event)
Description copied from interface: IMRParameterChangeListenerAPI
This is the main function of this interface. Any time a control paramater or independent paramater is changed by the user in a GUI this function is called, and a paramater change event is passed in. This function then determines what to do with the information ie. show some paramaters, set some as invisible, basically control the paramater lists.
Specified by:
parameterChange in interface IMRParameterChangeListenerAPI

synchVisible

public void synchVisible()
This is called when a user chooses a particular independent paramater as the x axis. What this does is make the independent paramater invisible in the paramater's variables list.
